Description: I am selling a used but in very good condition Fender American Special HSS Stratocaster. The guitar is Sunburst in color. I recently replaced the bridge and bridge block and added the wammy bar. It has a new set of D'Addario NY/XL 09/42 strings. It also includes a WolfPak Polyfoam travel case. NOTE: I have had a few questions regarding the serial number and Fenders system. There was a brief time in Fender's production between June of 2009, and March of 2010 where they were testing out a new S/N system. This system quickly got replaced, but some of the instruments during this time frame do not show up in the lookup tool. They are in Fender's data base but to run the S/N you need to call or email. I have attached both my original receipt from a very reputable re-seller here in Tulsa along with the email response I got back from Fender on the particulars of the instrument I am selling. If you have any doubt you can call or shoot Fender an email. They got back to me in less than a day with the one attached. Hope that clears it up. This is a beautiful guitar. Thanks for looking. Guitar Info Made by Fender, USA February 2010 Production Number: 594040 Neck is Rosewood. . From Fender: U.S. STRAT® POWER AND VALUE The American Special Stratocaster HSS puts U.S-made Fender quality into the hands of players at any level. For the guitarist who wants a combination of timeless Fender style and contemporary features, this guitar delivers traditional Strat® design with some extra elements for modern tone and performance, including Texas Special™ neck and middle pickups, a powerful humbucking bridge pickup, special circuitry, modern neck profile and fingerboard radius, and more. Great sounding, great looking and feeling, and made in the United States.
